More sophisticated underwriting models may be able to identify the creditworthy credit invisiblesinvisible primes.

We focus on 600-660 segment since 660 is typically the cutoff used by traditional lenders. (Ben-David, Johnson, Stulz)

600 lower bound since that is Upstarts minimum qualifying FICO score

The effects should be more pronounced for applicants with less than 600 FICO or no FICO.

If the lender is successful in identifying the invisible primes, then the FICO score should be less informative. The lender is sorting the applicants into different buckets within the same bucket based on traditional variables.

FICO regression / AUC

Upstart is able to identify different types of applicants with similar profiles in terms of traditional variables

Default probability regression / AUC

loans <- read_fst(path="/home/dimuthu/SSRN Oct 2021/Predictability/loans_2.fst",as.data.table = T)
loans[,log_odds:=log(default_probability/(1-default_probability))]
loans[,fico_cat:=ifelse(fico_score>=600 & fico_score<630,"600-629",
                        ifelse(fico_score<660,"630-659",
                               # ifelse(fico_score<660,"640-650",
                                      ifelse(fico_score<700,"660-699",
                                             ifelse(fico_score>=700,"700+",NA))))]

loans[,fico_cat:=ifelse(fico_score>=600 & fico_score<700,floor(fico_score/20)*20,
                        ifelse(fico_score>=700,700,NA))]

loans[,vantage_cat:=ifelse(vantage_score>=600 & fico_score<630,"600-629",
                        ifelse(vantage_score<660,"630-659",
                               # ifelse(fico_score<660,"640-650",
                                      ifelse(vantage_score<700,"660-699",
                                             ifelse(vantage_score>=700,"700+",NA))))]


loans[,pd_bin:=floor(default_probability*100/10)*10]
loans[,pd_bin:=ifelse(pd_bin>=50,50,pd_bin)]

1 Credit Score Predictability

controls = "+log(1+annual_income)+dti+borrower_age+I(borrower_age^2)+log(1+number_of_accounts)+log(1+inquiries_past_6_months)+log(1+total_balance)+log(1+credit_history)+log(1+num_accounts_opened_in_past_12_months)+log(1+revolving_pct*100)+log(1+mortgage_pct*100)+log(1+creditcard_utilization*100)+log(1+g051s_percentage_of_trades_ever_delinquent*100)"

covlabs <- c("log(Annual income)","Debt-to-income","Age of the borrower","Age of the borrower2","log(Number of accounts)","log(Number of inquiries)","log(Total liabilities)","log(Credit history)","log(No of recently opened accounts)","log(Pct. of revolving liabilities)","log(Pct. of mortgage liabilities)","log(Credit card utilization)","log(Pct. trades ever delinquent)","log(Loan amount)")

1.2 AUC

upstart_auc <- roc(delinquent24~fico_score,data=loans[accepted_date<="2020-03-31" & fico_score<660  & accepted_date>="2019-01-01"])

df <- data.table(x=1-upstart_auc$specificities,y=upstart_auc$sensitivities)

df[,model:=paste0("Credit score < 660: AUC=",round(roc(delinquent24~fico_score,data=loans[accepted_date<="2020-03-31" & fico_score<660  & accepted_date>="2019-01-01"])$auc[[1]]*100,0),"%")]


upstart_auc <- roc(delinquent24~fico_score,data=loans[accepted_date<="2020-03-31" & fico_score>=660  & accepted_date>="2019-01-01"])

temp <- data.table(x=1-upstart_auc$specificities,y=upstart_auc$sensitivities)

temp[,model:=paste0("Credit score >= 660: AUC=",round(roc(delinquent24~fico_score,data=loans[accepted_date<="2020-03-31" & fico_score>=660  & accepted_date>="2019-01-01"])$auc[[1]]*100,0),"%")]

df <- rbind(df,temp)
g1 <- ggplot(df,aes(x=x,y=y,color=model))+geom_line(aes(linetype=model),size=1)+theme_minimal()+labs(x="False Positive Rate",y="True Positive Rate")+geom_abline(intercept = 0,slope=1,aes(x=x,y=y))+scale_color_manual(values=c("dodgerblue4","dodgerblue2","black"))+theme(legend.position="bottom", legend.title = element_blank())+ guides(color = guide_legend(nrow = 2)) 

print(g1)

upstart_auc <- roc(delinquent24~default_probability,data=loans[accepted_date<="2020-03-31" & fico_score<660  & accepted_date>="2019-01-01"])

df <- data.table(x=1-upstart_auc$specificities,y=upstart_auc$sensitivities)

df[,model:=paste0("Credit score < 660: AUC=",round(roc(delinquent24~default_probability,data=loans[accepted_date<="2020-03-31" & fico_score<660  & accepted_date>="2019-01-01"])$auc[[1]]*100,0),"%")]


upstart_auc <- roc(delinquent24~default_probability,data=loans[accepted_date<="2020-03-31" & fico_score>=660  & accepted_date>="2019-01-01"])
